The paper studies the energy complexity of Boolean functions, which is a topic in computational complexity theory. Specifically, it explores the relationship between energy complexity and other well-studied parameters of Boolean functions, such as decision tree depth, sensitivity, and Karchmer-Wigderson game. This suggests that the paper could be categorized under cs.CC (Computational Complexity) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the paper introduces a new parameter called positive sensitivity, which is related to sensitivity and could be of interest to researchers in information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper also considers the energy complexity of Boolean formulas, which could be relevant to researchers in discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
